file path: api/README.md
content: # Curse Static Proxy

This project provides a simple and easy-to-use static web proxy.

## Usage

To use the proxy, simply send a GET request to the following endpoint:

```
https://<your-proxy-address>/<target-url>
```

For example, to proxy a request to the Google homepage, you would send a GET request to the following endpoint:

```
https://<your-proxy-address>/https://www.google.com
```

The proxy will then fetch the content from the target URL and return it to you.

## Features

* **Simple and easy to use:** Just send a GET request to the proxy endpoint and it will fetch the content from the target URL.
* **Supports all HTTP methods:** The proxy supports all HTTP methods, including GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE.
* **Rate limiting:** The proxy can be configured to rate limit requests to prevent abuse.
* **Customizable:** The proxy can be customized to your specific needs.

## Installation

To install the proxy, simply clone the GitHub repository and run the following command:

```
npm install
```

Once the proxy is installed, you can start it by running the following command:

```
node proxy.js
```

## Configuration

The proxy can be configured by editing the `config.js` file. The following options are available:

* **port:** The port that the proxy will listen on.
* **rateLimit:** The maximum number of requests that the proxy will allow per minute.
* **blacklist:** A list of URLs that the proxy will not proxy.

## Contributing

Contributions are welcome! Please read the [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/CurseStatic/web-proxy/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md) before submitting a pull request.